Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%grams} into 1cm chunks (no need to peel).

Halve and peel the @Red Onion{1}, then cut each half into 3 wedges.

Pop both veg onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @Oil{}, sprinkle over half
the @Roasted Spice and Herb Blend{1%sachet}, season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast the veg on the middle shelf until golden,
~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop the @Garlic Cloves{3}(unpeeled) into a small piece of #foil{} with
a drizzle of @Oil{} and scrunch to enclose it. Roast the parcel until soft,
~{10-12%minutes}.

While the potatoes bake, lay the @Salmon Fillets{2}, skin-side down, onto a
lined medium baking tray. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then sprinkle
over the remaining roasted herb and spice blend.

Roast the salmon on the top shelf until cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked
> when opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim the @Baby Cucumber{1}, then halve lengthways. Cut lengthways
into roughly 1cm wide strips, then cut into 1cm pieces widthways.

Add the cucumber to a large #bowl{} with the @Cider Vinegar{15%ml},
@Sugar{1/2%tsp} and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to combine.

Add the @Greek Style Natural Yoghurt{75%grams} to a small bowl.

Once the garlic has cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze it out of the
skin and mash with a #fork{}. Stir the roasted garlic into the yoghurt.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once cooked, drizzle half the @Red Pepper Chilli Jelly{25%grams} over the
salmon, then drizzle the remaining jelly over the veg. Toss the veg to coat.

Toss your @Baby Leaf Mix{50%grams} through the dressing.

Transfer your salmon and sticky veg to your #serving plates{}. Serve with the
salad alongside.

Drizzle over the garlic yoghurt to finish.

Enjoy!